criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Women between 25 and 50 years old with a diagnosis of CIN 2/3;

          -  Satisfactory colposcopy (squamocolumnar junction fully visible or partially visible);

          -  Negative pregnancy test result for women of childbearing potential;

          -  Be doing the first treatment for high-grade cervical intraepithelial lesion;

          -  Living 200 km or less from the city of Barretos-São Paulo / Brazil.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Women with suspected cervical cancer at colposcopy or biopsy;

          -  Pregnant or lactating patients;

          -  Patients with some immunodeficiency, transplanted or carrying the human
             immunodeficiency virus.
